%C A009982 The compositions of n in which each natural number is colored by one of p different colors are called p-colored compositions of n. For n >= 1, a(n) equals the number of 38-colored compositions of n such that no adjacent parts have the same color. - _Milan Janjic_, Nov 17 2011. [See A000244 for a proof.]
